pullRequest.body:
Some new API is introduced for subcomplexes of the standard simplex: any `S : Finset (Fin (n + 1))` defines a subcomplex `face S` of `Î”[n]`, and this face is isomorphic to `Î”[m]` when `Fin (m + 1) â‰ƒo S`. Then, boundaries and horns are redefined as subcomplexes of the standard simplex and it is shown that they are unions of certain codimension one faces of the standard simplex.

- [x] depends on: #21542
- [x] depends on: #21303
- [x] depends on: #21047

What explains the reason you need to annotate various simplicial sets as belonging to the type `SSet.{u}`? Is this to coerce a subcomplex of a simplex to a standard simplicial set?

> What explains the reason you need to annotate various simplicial sets as belonging to the type `SSet.{u}`? Is this to coerce a subcomplex of a simplex to a standard simplicial set?

Yes, this is to coerce subcomplexes to simplicial sets. (In some cases, the `(_ : SSet.{u})` syntax may not have been absolutely necesary, but this was also a way to clarify in which universe it was.)
